snippet: Offensive lineman Brandon Moore, who agreed to a deal with Dallas on Tuesday night, called the Cowboys on Wednesday with a change of heart, Coach Jason Garrett said.
abstract: NFL Roundup; former New York Jets offensive lineman Brandon Moore backs out of deal with Dallas Cowboys and plans to retire; other football developments noted.
lead_paragraph: Offensive lineman Brandon Moore, who agreed to a deal with Dallas on Tuesday night, called the Cowboys on Wednesday with a change of heart, Coach Jason Garrett said.

headline.main: Set to Play for Dallas, Ex-Jet Elects to Retire
headline.print_headline: Having Agreed to Play for Dallas, Ex-Jet Elects to Retire
